= [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] Conference

Wilhelm Marx, former [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] chancellor and presidential candidate, has chosen to resign from leadership of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?]. Now, the party holds a conference to replace him.

The consensus candidate on the right is Ludwig Kaas, a Catholic priest who represents the party's traditionalists. On the other hand, there is Fin55, a leader of the Catholic trade unions and synthesizer of Papal-Stalinism, who has been more supportive of cooperation with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> than most of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?]. [? if not prussia_leader == "Bee": Train Lover Bee has fallen to a distant third, making it highly unlikely that he will win the leadership.?][? if prussia_leader == "Bee": Train union chairman and Minister-President Bee has lost some ground, but he retains strong support from the Choo-Choo branch of the party, effectively securing him the nomination. ?]

- @kaas: The [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] elects Ludwig Kaas as the party chair.
- @fin55: Influence the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] to select Fin55 as the party chair.
- @fin55_campaign: We must hold a campaign in support of Fin55 as party chair.
- @bee: The [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] chooses Bee as the party chair, the trains WILL run on time.

@kaas
view-if: not prussia_leader == "Bee"
on-arrival: z_leader = "Kaas"; z_relation -= 5; prussian_concordat_progress += 1; z_ideology = "Right"
face-image: img/portraits/Ludwig_Kaas.jpg

Ludwig Kaas has been selected as the chairman of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?]. He seems to represent a rightward turn from Marx, and will preside over a [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] less inclined to compromise with the left. 

Despite this, Kaas is committed to the current constitutional order and the republic. He maintains a close friendship with Eugenio Pacelli, the Papal Nuncio to Germany, which may prove useful during concordat negotiations.

@fin55
unavailable-subtitle: Fin is tired of the weekly religion debates.
subtitle: Fin is likely to be friendlier to us than Kaas.
view-if: not prussia_leader == "Bee"
choose-if: z_relation >= 60
on-arrival: z_leader = "Fin55"; z_ideology = "Left"; catholics_z -= 3; catholics_dnvp += 2; catholics_other += 2; catholics_spd += 5; workers_z += 5; z_relation += 4; zentrum_disintegration += 1; dvp_left += 1; ddp_left += 1; ddp_cohesion += 1; lvp_left += 1
face-image: img/portraits/Joseph_Joos.jpg

With our grassroots connections, we have been able to influence the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] delegates to support Fin55 as the new [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] chairman. He has long been a friend of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, and will be more inclined to collaborate with us compared to Kaas. He also increases the appeal of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] to the working class, though it comes at the cost of deepening the social and economic divisions once held together by religion.

@fin55_campaign
