With our grassroots connections as well as a professional campaign, we have been able to influence the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] delegates to support Fin55 as the new [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] chairman. He has long been a friend of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, and will be more inclined to collaborate with us compared to Kaas. He also increases the appeal of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] to the working class, though it comes at the cost of deepening the social and economic divisions once held together by religion.

@bee
