Bee has been elected as the chairman of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?]. He seems to represent a rightward turn from Marx, despite his trade union background, and will preside over a [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] less inclined to compromise with the left. He views the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] as a prototype for a <span style="color: #000000;">Christian</span>, <span style="color: #586593;">democratic</span>, <span style="color: #000000;">German</span>, and <span style="color: #c00000;">social</span> party, and aims to transform it according to the principles laid out in his proposed "Train program" eight years prior. 

The [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?]'s middle class wing are in uproar over the vote, despite Bee conceding his leadership of the Reichstag delegation and the Minister-Presidency to his protege Heinrich Brüning. [? if dnvp_ideology == "Radical": His election also attracts some Protestant <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> dissidents and industrialists, who may result in a shift of the party towards the right. ?]
